== DESCRIPTION

Inochi is an infrastructure that helps you create, test, document, package,
publish, and announce your <<Ruby>> projects.

=== Features

* Provides a comprehensive help manual that is written in <<eRuby>> over
  <<AsciiDoc>> and is rendered into a Web page and a UNIX manual page.

* Announces project releases on <<RAA>>, <<ruby-talk>>, and via RSS feed.

* Stores project information in a single Ruby source file.

=== Resources

Project website::
<%= @proj_home_url = Inochi::WEBSITE %>

Announcements feed::
<%= @ann_feed_url = File.join(@proj_home_url, 'ann.xml') %>

API documentation::
<%= @api_docs_url = File.join(@proj_home_url, 'api/') %>

Source code (browse online, download, or checkout)::
<%= @code_repo_url = 'http://github.com/sunaku/inochi' %>

Issue tracker (report bugs, request features, get help)::
<%= @bug_track_url = File.join(@code_repo_url, 'issues') %>
